>>>>>>> Here at Diabetes UK Cymru we offer support to everyone affected by
diabetes, whether you or someone you know has just been diagnosed, if you have
been living with Type 1 or Type 2 diabetes for a while or if you’re a
>>>>>>> Here are some of the ways that we can help:
>>>>>>> As well as lots of great information on our online guide to diabetes
we have a range of informative brochures and printed materials about living
with diabetes that you may find useful. If you want us to send these out to
you then please let us know by calling us on 029 2066 8276 or email
>>>>>>> Our Helpline is staffed by trained advisors with counselling skills,
talk to us for advice and support by calling 0345 123 2399. The service is
available between 9am and 7pm on Monday to Friday.
>>>>>>> If you want talk to someone with diabetes we have English and Welsh
speaking trained volunteers who have first-hand experience of diabetes. Our
peer support service is for everyone living with diabetes in Wales, including
parents of children with diabetes. You can get in touch by calling 0843 353
8600 or find out more about Peer Support.
>>>>>>> We have a range of adult groups across Wales that provide face to face
support for anyone living with diabetes, informative discussions and talks
from experts. We also have family groups where parents and children meet to
>>>>>>> Go to our Local Groups page to find your nearest one.
>>>>>>> If you are struggling to resolve a specific issue relating to your
diabetes then we may be able to help. Please email wales@diabetes.org.uk for
>>>>>>> Keep checking the Events pages on our Diabetes UK Cymru site to see
whether we have any care events coming up in your area.
